Did a set of 5 plates before this hoping it would feel light weight baby, but it was definitely heavy weight daddy so decided to torture myself with some high volume squats immediately after💀

🚨ALSO got something really exciting coming up, me and @melissabum are going to be having a transformation contest. With most peoples gyms opening back up it’s the perfect time to start some good habits and get back in shape or into your best shape.
You’ll be getting nutrition and training plans as well as check ins from either myself or Melissa to guide you through the process. We’re going to make it a fun sibling rivalry of team MelBum vs team Cbum with prizes for the best transformation.
With myself starting prep in a few weeks as well it’ll be like you guys are prepping with me.
I’ll have a lot more info to come at the beginning of next week so if your interested keep an eye out for the announcement👀

node.text:
Just uploaded a special video on YouTube got the whole fam involved for a fun little Q&A (link is in my bio).
One of the questions was, what’s our favorite part about prepping for the Olympia, and my cheesiness came up with the answer “that it brings us all together a lot more for moments like these”.
I couldn’t be more grateful for the support, love and understanding from my family during such an important time in our lives (especially the understanding when I’m being extra “sharp”😅).
Having so much positive support is an immeasurable advantage, so when we’re all together you better watch out 😉

node.text:
All right so because everyone loves free shit and I love you guys, here’s a chance to win some awesome free shit. No strings attached.
I’m teaming up with @eleikosport (super high quality weight lifting equipment manufacturer) and @gymshark to give away the following:
1. First winner gets $3,000 gift card for @eleikosport and a $300 @gymshark gift card.
2. The next two winners each get a $1,000 gift card for Eleiko and and a $200 Gymshark gift card.
To enter all you have to do is like this post and tag 2 friends.
That’s it.
I’ll be reaching out the winners in one week!
Trying to find all the ways I can to give back to you guys to at least begin to try and show how grateful I am for all the support❤️
T&C’s found on Eleiko’s website🙏🏼

node.text:
When I first switched over to Classic Physique I was shitty poser and a classic broke college student.
I couldn’t afford big fancy mirrors to practice, but luckily I found someone throwing away some old mirrored closet doors. I snagged them and set them up in my bedroom.
I pushed all my furniture in the corner, put my headphones on and taught myself how to pose by practicing every day.
Fast forward a few Olympias later and I felt it was only right to order some closet doors and continue to perfect what I was just learning back in 2016.
I honestly never imagined I would end up where I am, I was just taking it one step at a day and enjoying every second of it.
From that kid who should’ve been studying for exams posing in his college room, to stepping on the @mrolympiallc stage for the fifth time.
I am so grateful for every moment and opportunity that has lead me to where I am today, it’s a damn beautiful life.

A whole bunch of rows🤷🏻‍♀️
All my workouts are uploaded daily (slightly delayed) onto my @cbumfitness training app.
There are currently 6 splits to choose from, but I am personally following the “Olympia Prep” split (duhh).
Check it out at cbumfitness.com 🙏🏼
